The evidence with the title 'Trends in U.S. military spending | council on foreign relations ' says Jul 15, 2014  ... When U.S. inflation - adjusted military spending fell by one - third in the 1990s , the U.S. share of global military spending only fell bysixpercentage ... Between 1990 and 1995 , cuts in foreign allocation of gdp to defense ( especially in Russia ) boosted the U.S. share of total military spending (the green bar). 
